The paper presents a new algorithm for identifying the transition and emission probabilities of a hidden Markov model (HMM) from the emitted data, which is a problem in machine learning and statistics. The paper also applies the method to hidden topic Markov modeling, which is a subfield of natural language processing and information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves statistical analysis and information theory, which are related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
